Below are **free, printable/downloadable** resources that stay very close to **SOF IMO (Class/Grade 5)** in format (mostly timed, mixed-topic, multiple-choice / olympiad-style reasoning).

## 1) Official SOF IMO (Class 5) resources

- **SOF IMO Class 5 syllabus + exam pattern/marking scheme (Level 1)** (use this to build your topic checklist and pacing). citeturn1view1  
- **SOF IMO Sample Paper (Class 5, 2025–26) — PDF** (includes sample questions + marking scheme + syllabus + answer key). citeturn2view0  
- **SOF Sample OMR sheet — PDF** (use this to practice bubbling + time discipline). citeturn14search10  
- **SOF “How to prepare” guidance page** (high-level prep guidance straight from SOF). citeturn17search10  
- **SOF IMO Set-A answer keys page (PDF downloads by class)** (useful only if you already have the corresponding question paper). citeturn17search9  

## 2) SOF-aligned free practice (SOF-focused providers)

- **SOF Olympiad Trainer (Class 5 IMO) Sample Paper — PDF** (SOF-style; quick extra copy of the sample paper). citeturn4view0  
- **SOF Olympiad Trainer Sample OMR Sheet — PDF** citeturn4view1  
- **MTG “Class 5 IMO – 4 Years Sample Paper” free eBook — PDF** (more SOF-style questions; good volume). citeturn14search19  

## 3) Very close “same lane” alternatives (upper-primary olympiad papers with free PDFs)

These are excellent because they keep the **same kind of mixed reasoning + arithmetic/geometry/data** feel, without jumping too far in difficulty.

### A) Primary Mathematics Challenge (PMC) — The Mathematical Association (UK)
- **PMC downloads hub** (multiple years’ papers + answers/notes + bonus rounds). citeturn6view0  
- **PMC Nov 2022 Paper — PDF** (25 questions; timed; mostly multiple-choice + a few short answers). citeturn28view0  
- **PMC Nov 2022 Answers & Notes — PDF** citeturn28view1  
- **PMC Bonus Round Feb 2023 Paper — PDF** citeturn28view2  
- **PMC Bonus Round Feb 2023 Answers/Notes — PDF** citeturn28view3  

### B) UKMT Primary Kangaroo (UK) — free past paper set
- **Primary Kangaroo 2025 Questions — PDF** citeturn8view0  
- **Primary Kangaroo 2025 Solutions — PDF** citeturn8view1  
- **Primary Kangaroo practice answer sheet — PDF** citeturn9view0  

## 4) Strong olympiad-style problem solving (Grades 4–6 range) with free downloads

### A) MOEMS (Math Olympiads for Elementary & Middle Schools, US)
- **MOEMS Resources page** (includes **free sample contests** for Division E (Grades 4–6) and Division M (Grades 6–8), plus links to archived “Problem of the Week” + solutions). citeturn26view0  
- **Sample Contest Division E (Grades 4–6) — PDF (Google Drive link)** citeturn27view0  
- **Sample Contest Division M — PDF (Google Drive link)** (harder; use as “stretch”). citeturn27view1  

### B) APSMO (Australian Primary Schools Maths Olympiad) — sample PDFs from olympiad-problem volumes
- **MOCP Volume 1 sample — PDF** citeturn25search7  
- **MOCP Volume 3 sample — PDF** citeturn25search4  

---

If you want, I can also turn this into a **simple 6–8 week practice sequence** (what to do each week using only the links above), but the list above is already enough to run a full prep program.
